<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 11:06PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Paulding, northeastern Haralson, northeastern Carroll and western
Douglas Counties through 1130 PM EDT...
At 1106 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Lake Val-Do-Mar, or 8
miles west of Douglasville, moving northwest at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Douglasville, Buchanan, Villa Rica, Bremen, Temple, Yorkville,
Draketown, Winston, Lake Val-Do-Mar, Eubank Lake, New Georgia and
Bill Arp.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
